
[1]chronicle

   CHRONICLE, n. [See Chronic.]

   1. A historical account of facts or events disposed in the order of
   time. It is nearly synonymous with annals. In general, this species of
   writing is more strictly confined to chronological order, and is less
   diffuse than the form of writing called history.

   2. In a more general sense, a history.

   3. That which contains history.

   Europe - her very ruins tell the history of times gone by, and every
   moldering stone is a chronicle.

   4. Chronicles, plu. Two books of the Old Testament.

      CHRONICLE, v.t. To record in history, or chronicle; to record; to
                                  register.
